-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item (most recent)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/marts/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate return rates by product category
WITH items_with_returns AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.quantity,
        p.product_id,
        c.name AS category_name,
        CASE
            WHEN dr.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1
            ELSE 0
        END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
        ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
    SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN is_returned = 1 THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    CASE
        WHEN SUM(quantity) = 0 THEN 0
        ELSE SUM(CASE WHEN is_returned = 1 THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) * 1.0 / SUM(quantity)
    END AS return_rate
FROM items_with_returns
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)')
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
